# write-or-die — Project Knowledge

A SvelteKit 5 (Svelte runes) "write or die" forced-writing app. Keep typing or your text fades and gets wiped.

## Stack

- SvelteKit 2 + Svelte 5 (runes: `$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`, `$props`)
- Vite 7, Vitest (browser + node projects), Playwright e2e, ESLint + Prettier
- Deploy adapter: `@sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare` (build output: `.svelte-kit/cloudflare`)
- Node v24.x, npm. Indentation: tabs.

## Key files

- `src/routes/+page.svelte` — entire app. FSM with `phase`: `idle → writing → danger → done`.
  - `writing`: main countdown; each keystroke resets a 2s idle watchdog.
  - `danger`: paused main timer, text fades (`textOpacity = dangerTimer / 10`), wiped after 10s.
  - `done`: download text as `write-or-die.txt`.
  - Anti-cheat: blocks paste/copy/right-click; tab-switch or window blur while writing wipes text.
- `src/lib/persisted.svelte.js` — `$state` + `localStorage` wrapper (persists `timeInvestedInWritingSoFar`).
- `src/lib/components/SetTimerButton.svelte` — timer-preset button.

## Commands

- Dev: `npm run dev` (`-- --open` to open browser)
- Build / preview: `npm run build` / `npm run preview`
- Lint / format: `npm run lint` / `npm run format`
- Tests: `npm run test` (unit then e2e), `npm run test:unit`, `npm run test:e2e`

## Deployment (IMPORTANT)

Deployed via **Cloudflare "Workers & Pages" Git integration** connected to GitHub
repo `eric-akira/write-or-die`. Cloudflare **builds from source on every push to `main`**
(build command `npm run build`, output dir `.svelte-kit/cloudflare`).

- To deploy: `git push origin main` (no manual build/upload step).
- There is **no `wrangler.toml`/`wrangler.jsonc`** in the repo, so local `wrangler deploy`
  (Workers) is not configured. Do not assume CLI deploy works without adding config.

See `COMMANDS.md` for the full cheat sheet.
